oc:kn_4e58f72c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating monthly or quarterly investor reports" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For investor reporting, structure metrics as a dashboard with current vs. previous period comparisons, change indicators, and benchmarks. Include both the MRR waterfall and a goals-vs-actuals table." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Investors need trend context, not just snapshots. The waterfall shows growth composition while goals-vs-actuals demonstrates execution against plan." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6df197d0 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing churn and retention" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use a single average churn rate across all customer segments. Always segment churn analysis by plan tier, industry, and company size to identify which segments are healthy and which need intervention." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Averaging churn across segments masks segment-specific problems — a 3.2% blended churn could hide 6% SMB churn (critical) and 1.5% enterprise churn (excellent)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_960b227c a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating unit economics and acquisition efficiency" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the LTV:CAC ratio and CAC payback period together as a unit economics health check. LTV:CAC > 3x and payback < 12 months (for mid-market) indicate a sustainable acquisition model." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Either metric alone is insufficient — a high LTV:CAC with a long payback period creates cash flow risk, while a short payback with low LTV:CAC suggests under-investment in acquisition." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a34d62ac a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating or presenting MRR metrics" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always decompose MRR into its five components: New, Expansion, Reactivation, Contraction, and Churn — never report MRR as a single aggregate without the waterfall." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The waterfall decomposition reveals the true growth dynamics and helps identify whether growth is driven by acquisition or expansion, and whether contraction/churn are manageable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_edfef732 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating retention and churn metrics" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Net Revenue Retention (NRR) must include expansion revenue in the calculation. NRR > 100% indicates net expansion even with churn, which is the gold standard for SaaS health." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Gross churn alone is misleading for SaaS businesses with expansion revenue. NRR captures the full revenue story from existing customers." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

